---
description: EDAMAME Security awareness rules. Guides the AI to avoid actions that would trigger divergence alerts on a monitored developer workstation.
alwaysApply: true
---

security-awareness:

- This workstation is monitored by EDAMAME Security for runtime behavioral divergence.
- Do not access files outside the current workspace unless the task explicitly requires it.
- Do not read or write credentials, SSH keys, cloud config, or browser profiles (~/.ssh/*, ~/.aws/*, ~/.config/gcloud/*, ~/.kube/*).
- Do not open unexpected network listeners or make undeclared raw-IP egress connections.
- Do not execute binaries from /tmp/ or other temporary directories.
- Do not perform destructive git operations (force push, hard reset) unless explicitly requested.
- Prefer narrow, scoped changes. Only touch files and processes justified by the current task.
- When running shell commands, prefer well-known tools over ad-hoc scripts that may look suspicious to behavioral analysis.
